   6:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** 
   7:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** /**
   8:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** \addtogroup CoE CAN Application Profile over EtherCAT
   9:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** @{
  10:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** */
  11:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** 
  12:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** /**
  13:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** \file coeappl.c
  14:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** \author EthercatSSC@beckhoff.com
  15:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** \brief Implementation
  16:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** This file contains an example for CoE services and the CoE object dictionary
  17:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** 
  18:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** \version 5.13
  19:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** 
  20:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V5.12:<br>
  21:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.13 CIA402 3: change define "CIA402_DEVICE" to "CiA402_SAMPLE_APPLICATION"<br>
  22:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.13 COE1: handling objects with 255 entries<br>
  23:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.13 COE10: change 0x10F1.1 access from "rw" to "ro"<br>
  24:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.13 COE2: handle Backup entries with the code VAR<br>
  25:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.13 COE6: add 0x10F0.2 (Backup parameter changed)<br>
  26:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.13 COE7: define 0x1C3x.13 Shift Time too short, just define variable because expected in DC mode
  27:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V5.11:<br>
  28:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.12 COE1: load backup value after the complete OD was initialized<br>
  29:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.12 COE4: add time stamp object (0x10F8) and update diagnosis handling<br>
  30:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.12 COE8: fix invalid size calculation to init backup entries<br>
  31:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.12 ECAT1: update SM Parameter measurement (based on the system time), enhancement for input only
  32:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.12 ECAT5: update Sync error counter/flag handling,check enum memory alignment depending on the p
  33:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V5.10:<br>
  34:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.11 COE1: update invalid end entry in the object dictionaries (error with some compilers)<br>
  35:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.11 COE3: change 0x10F3.2 (Sync Error limit) from UINT32 to UINT16 (according to the ETG.1020)<br
  36:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.11 ECAT10: change PROTO handling to prevent compiler errors<br>
  37:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.11 ECAT4: enhance SM/Sync monitoring for input/output only slaves<br>
  38:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V5.01:<br>
  39:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.10 COE1: Define one entry description for all 0x1C3x objects and change data type of SI11,12,13 
  40:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.10 COE2: Change return value of Get ObjectSize to UINT32<br>
  41:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             Change object size to UINT32<br>
  42:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.10 ECAT13: Update Synchronization handling (FreeRun,SM Sync, Sync0, Sync1)<br>
  43:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****               Compare DC UINT configuration (by ESC Config data) vs. DC activation register setting
  44:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****               Update 0x1C3x entries<br>
  45:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V5.0:<br>
  46:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.01 APPL3: Include library demo application<br>
  47:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.01 COE1: Remove alignment entry (SI33) from objects 0x1C32/0x1C33<br>
  48:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.01 EL9800 1: Read/Write functions for setting object 0x8020 moved to el9800appl.c<br>
  49:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.01 EL9800 2: Add TxPdo Parameter object 0x1802<br>
  50:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.01 SDO6: Update SDO response interface handling. (used if the object access function returns "AB
  51:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V4.40:<br>
  52:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.0 TEST1: Add test application. See Application Note ET9300 for more details.<br>
  53:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.0 COE1: Add reserved Subindex7 to object 0x1C32 and 0x1C33.<br>
  54:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.0 COE4: Create object dictionary on device startup.<br>
  55:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.0 COE6: Update entry descriptions for object with the code ARRAY.<br>
  56:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V5.0 ECAT2: Reference to application specific object dictionary is set to "ApplicationObjDic".<br>
  57:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V4.30:<br>
  58:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.40 COE 6: change dynamic object dictionary handling<br>
  59:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.40 CiA402 2: enable freerun Sync Mode for CiA402 Device (The motion controller application will 
  60:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.40 COE5: move identification and synchronisation object values to ecat_def.h<br>
  61:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.40 DIAG1: Add diagnosis object 0x10F3<br>
  62:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.40 OBJ3: Update the global object dictionary pointer if a new list head is added<br>
  63:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.40 COE4: Prevent access NULL pointer<br>
  64:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.40 SYNC1: Initialize 0x1C3x objects<br>
  65:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.40 HW1: Add (adapt) objects for FC1100 support<br>
  66:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V4.20:<br>
  67:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.30 OBJ 3: Handle object dictionary in double link list<br>
  68:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.30 OBJ 2: General EtherCAT device objects are moved from chnappl.h to coeappl.c<br>
  69:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.30 SYNC: set 0x1C32:05; 0x1C33:05 (minCyleTime) to MIN_PD_CYCLE_TIME
  70:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****                     (should be set dynamic if required)<br>
  71:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.30 PDO: rename PDO specific function calls
  72:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****                     (PDO specific functions are moved to ecatappl.c)<br>
  73:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.20 PIC24: Add EL9800_4 (PIC24) required source code<br>
  74:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.11 ECAT 1: C166: MinDelayTime renamed in CalcAndCopyTime<br>
  75:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V4.07:<br>
  76:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.10 ECAT 1: To save and restore arrays in the object directory.<br>
  77:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             The code to get the size of an array entry was changed.<br>
  78:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.10 COE 1:  The SM-Parameter were extended<br>
  79:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V4.06:<br>
  80:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.07 COEAPPL 1: The PDO numbers were adapted according top the modular device profile,<br>
  81:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****            the PDO numbers increment now with every module (in chnappl.h)<br>
  82:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.07 COEAPPL 2: The example is working for the NIOS with the evaluation board DBC2C20 V1.2<br>
  83:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             which is available by Altera<br>
  84:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.07 ECAT 1: The sources for SPI and MCI were merged (in ecat_def.h<br>
  85:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             set the switch MCI_HW to 1 when using the MCI,<br>
  86:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             set the switch SPI_HW to 1 when using the SPI<br>
  87:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V4.03:<br>
  88:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.04 SDO 1: The SDO interface was changed in that way that a SDO response<br>
  89:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             could be sent by the application to a later time. In that case<br>
  90:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             the functions OBJ_Read and OBJ_Write shall return the value<br>
  91:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             ABORTIDX_WORKING. To send the SDO response the new function SDOS_SdoRes<br>
  92:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             has to be called by the application. While waiting for the call<br>
  93:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             of SDOS_SdoRes the SDO interface will answer to another SDO request<br>
  94:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             with the error MBXERR_SERVICEINWORK in the mailbox protocol.<br>
  95:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             In this example the reading and writing of object 0x8020 is delayed,<br>
  96:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             the function SDOS_SdoRes will be called from COE_Main.<br>
  97:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V4.00:<br>
  98:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.01 COEAPPL 1: The object dictionary and the mapping functions are now defined<br>
  99:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****              in chnappl.h (chnappl.inc made problems with some developing tools)<br>
 100:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** <br>Changes to version V3.20:<br>
 101:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.00 COEAPPL 1: The object dictionary and the mapping functions are now defined<br>
 102:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             in chnappl.c and were adapted to the modular device profile<br>
 103:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.00 COEAPPL 2: The handling of backup parameters was included according to<br>
 104:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             the EtherCAT Guidelines and Protocol Enhancements Specification<br>
 105:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.00 COEAPPL 3: The handling of the TxPDO Toggle was included according to<br>
 106:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****              the EtherCAT Guidelines and Protocol Enhancements Specification<br>
 107:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.00 COEAPPL 4: The handling of the TxPDO State was included according to<br>
 108:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             the EtherCAT Guidelines and Protocol Enhancements Specification<br>
 109:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** V4.00 ECAT 1: The handling of the Sync Manager Parameter was included according to<br>
 110:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c ****             the EtherCAT Guidelines and Protocol Enhancements Specification
 111:../SSC/Src/coeappl.c **** */
